@tibuch you might look into adding it following for example the `get_rng_state` function.
The python bindings are written in [here](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/csrc/cuda/Module.cpp#L177-L185), and then registered in [here](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/csrc/cuda/Module.cpp#L377), so that they are visible from the python side in the [`_C` module](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/cuda/random.py#L18).
This will require though some familiarity with writing Python C extensions.
